prior_1:
Imagine a man and a woman who both work for the same airline in the United States. One person is a pilot and the other person is a flight attendant, but you don't know which person has which job. Please guess the answers to both the questions below. 
Because there are two hypotheses—either one of them is the pilot (and the other is the flight attendant)—both estimates have to sum to 100%. Don't worry about doing the math, once you position the first slider, the second slider will only allow you to enter enough so that they both add up to 100% - Chance that the man is the pilot
